# ffuf — Fast Web Fuzzer

## What is ffuf

ffuf (Fuzz Faster U Fool) is a fast and highly flexible web fuzzer written in Go. It can fuzz directories, files, parameters, headers, subdomains, virtual hosts, and any other part of an HTTP request using the keyword `FUZZ` as a placeholder.

---

## Installation

```bash
# Kali Linux
sudo apt install ffuf

# From source
go install github.com/ffuf/ffuf/v2@latest

# Verify
ffuf -V
```

---

## Core Concept

Place the word `FUZZ` anywhere in a request. ffuf replaces it with every line from your wordlist.

```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt
```

---

## Directory and File Fuzzing

```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ \
     -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt
```

### With file extensions

```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ \
     -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/raft-large-words.txt \
     -e .php,.html,.txt,.bak,.zip,.conf
```

---

## Common Flags

| Flag | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `-u` | Target URL |
| `-w` | Wordlist (use `wordlist.txt:KEYWORD` for multiple) |
| `-e` | File extensions to append |
| `-t` | Threads (default 40) |
| `-o` | Output file |
| `-of` | Output format: json, csv, html, md |
| `-mc` | Match HTTP status codes |
| `-ms` | Match response size |
| `-ml` | Match number of lines |
| `-fc` | Filter out status codes |
| `-fs` | Filter out response size |
| `-fl` | Filter out line count |
| `-H` | Add header |
| `-b` | Add cookie |
| `-X` | HTTP method |
| `-d` | POST data |
| `-r` | Follow redirects |
| `-v` | Verbose output |
| `-ac` | Auto-calibrate filters |

