## Filtering Responses

The most important skill in ffuf. You need to filter noise to find real results.

### Filter by status code

```bash
# Only show 200 responses
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -mc 200

# Hide 404 responses
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -fc 404
```

### Filter by response size

If all false positives have the same size (e.g. 1495 bytes):
```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -fs 1495
```

### Auto-calibrate (best for beginners)

ffuf automatically detects and filters false positives:
```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -ac
```

