## Parameter Fuzzing

Find hidden GET parameters:
```bash
ffuf -u "http://target.com/page?FUZZ=value" \
     -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/burp-parameter-names.txt \
     -fs 1234
```

Find parameter values:
```bash
ffuf -u "http://target.com/page?id=FUZZ" \
     -w /usr/share/seclists/Fuzzing/numbers.txt
```

POST data fuzzing:
```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/login \
     -X POST \
     -d "username=admin&password=FUZZ" \
     -w /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt \
     -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" \
     -fc 401
```

---

## Virtual Host Fuzzing

Find virtual hosts on a target IP:
```bash
ffuf -u http://10.10.10.10 \
     -H "Host: FUZZ.target.com" \
     -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt \
     -fs 1234
```

The `-fs` here filters the default response size so only different (real) vhosts show up.

---

## Multiple Wordlists

Use `W1`, `W2` as keywords with multiple wordlists:
```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/W1/W2 \
     -w dirs.txt:W1 \
     -w files.txt:W2
```

---

## Saving Output

```bash
ffuf -u http://target.com/FUZZ \
     -w wordlist.txt \
     -o results.json \
     -of json
```

---

## Recommended Wordlists
common.txt                          — fast directory discovery

raft-large-words.txt                — thorough directory discovery

raft-large-files.txt                — file discovery

burp-parameter-names.txt            — parameter fuzzing

subdomains-top1million-5000.txt     — vhost/subdomain fuzzing

---

## CTF Tips

- Use `-ac` on CTF boxes — it auto-filters noise very well
- Always fuzz for file extensions on PHP boxes: `-e .php,.bak,.txt`
- Parameter fuzzing often reveals hidden admin features
- Combine vhost fuzzing with `/etc/hosts` entries to access discovered hosts

